name: tRNA dimethylallyltransferase
classes: Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
reaction: dimethylallyl diphosphate + adenine37 in tRNA = diphosphate + N6-dimethylallyladenine37 in tRNA [RN:R01122]
comment: Formerly known as tRNA isopentenyltransferase (EC 2.5.1.8), but it is now known that dimethylallyl diphosphate, rather than isopentenyl diphosphate, is the substrate.

references.title: Regulation of substrate recognition by the MiaA tRNA prenyltransferase modification enzyme of Escherichia coli K-12.
